import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from datetime import datetime

# Load dataset
df = pd.read_csv("/Users/rero/.cache/kagglehub/datasets/berkeleyearth/climate-change-earth-surface-temperature-data/versions/2/GlobalTemperatures.csv")
df = df[["dt", "LandAverageTemperature"]].dropna()
df["dt"] = pd.to_datetime(df["dt"])
df = df[df["dt"] >= "1900-01-01"]

# Resample to monthly average (cleaner)
df.set_index("dt", inplace=True)
monthly_temp = df["LandAverageTemperature"].resample("ME").mean()

# Normalize (for visual purposes only)
normalized_temp = (monthly_temp - monthly_temp.mean()) / monthly_temp.std()

# Pick a time window for visualization
window_start = "2000-01-01"
window_end = "2010-12-01"
plot_series = normalized_temp[window_start:window_end]

# Simulate forecasting
forecast_horizon = 12
train_series = plot_series[:-forecast_horizon]
forecast_series = plot_series[-forecast_horizon:]

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
plt.plot(train_series.index, train_series, label="Input Sequence", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_series.index, forecast_series, label="Forecast Target", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.axvline(forecast_series.index[0], color="gray", linestyle=":", label="Forecast Start")
plt.title("Input and Forecast Horizon for TCN Model")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Normalized Temperature")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("slide4_tcn_input_forecast.png", dpi=300)
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load country-level data
df = pd.read_csv("/Users/rero/.cache/kagglehub/datasets/berkeleyearth/climate-change-earth-surface-temperature-data/versions/2/GlobalLandTemperaturesByCountry.csv")
df = df.dropna(subset=["AverageTemperature"])

# Focus on a temperate country with clear seasonal variation
df = df[df["Country"] == "Canada"]
df["dt"] = pd.to_datetime(df["dt"])
df = df[df["dt"].dt.year >= 1900]

# Create month-year field
df["year"] = df["dt"].dt.year
df["month"] = df["dt"].dt.month

# Monthly average per year (to preserve seasonal pattern)
monthly_avg = df.groupby(["year", "month"])["AverageTemperature"].mean().unstack()

# Set up plot
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 6))
sns.set(style="whitegrid")

# Plot a few sample decades
decades = [1920, 1960, 2000, 2020]
colors = ["#4c72b0", "#55a868", "#c44e52", "#8172b3"]

for i, decade in enumerate(decades):
    if decade in monthly_avg.index:
        plt.plot(range(1, 13), monthly_avg.loc[decade], label=f"{decade}", color=colors[i], linewidth=2.5)

plt.title("Seasonal Temperature Patterns in Canada (By Decade)", fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel("Month", fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel("Average Temperature (°C)", fontsize=12)
plt.xticks(range(1, 13))
plt.legend(title="Decade")
plt.grid(True, linestyle="--", alpha=0.4)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("slide5_lstm_regime_shift.png", dpi=300)
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load major city and country data
city_df = pd.read_csv("/Users/rero/.cache/kagglehub/datasets/berkeleyearth/climate-change-earth-surface-temperature-data/versions/2/GlobalLandTemperaturesByMajorCity.csv")
country_df = pd.read_csv("/Users/rero/.cache/kagglehub/datasets/berkeleyearth/climate-change-earth-surface-temperature-data/versions/2/GlobalLandTemperaturesByCountry.csv")

# Focus on Toronto (urban) and Canada (country)
city_df = city_df[(city_df["City"] == "Toronto") & (city_df["Country"] == "Canada")].dropna(subset=["AverageTemperature"])
country_df = country_df[country_df["Country"] == "Canada"].dropna(subset=["AverageTemperature"])

# Convert dates
city_df["dt"] = pd.to_datetime(city_df["dt"])
country_df["dt"] = pd.to_datetime(country_df["dt"])

# Align date range
start_year = 1900
city_df = city_df[city_df["dt"].dt.year >= start_year]
country_df = country_df[country_df["dt"].dt.year >= start_year]

# Monthly average for matching comparison
city_monthly = city_df.set_index("dt")["AverageTemperature"].resample("ME").mean()
country_monthly = country_df.set_index("dt")["AverageTemperature"].resample("ME").mean()

# Align both time series
combined = pd.DataFrame({
    "Toronto": city_monthly,
    "Canada": country_monthly
}).dropna()

# Compute urban heat island effect
combined["Difference"] = combined["Toronto"] - combined["Canada"]

# Rolling average to smooth
combined["SmoothedDiff"] = combined["Difference"].rolling(window=12, center=True).mean()

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 5))
sns.set(style="whitegrid")
plt.plot(combined.index, combined["SmoothedDiff"], label="Urban Heat Island Effect (Toronto - Canada)", color="darkred")
plt.axhline(0, linestyle="--", color="gray", alpha=0.6)
plt.title("Urban Heat Island Effect: Toronto vs. Canada (Smoothed Monthly Difference)", fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel("Year")
plt.ylabel("Temperature Difference (°C)")
plt.legend()
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("slide6_convlstm_heatmap.png", dpi=300)
plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load global temperature data
df = pd.read_csv("/Users/rero/.cache/kagglehub/datasets/berkeleyearth/climate-change-earth-surface-temperature-data/versions/2/GlobalTemperatures.csv")

# Monthly average

monthly_temp = df["LandAverageTemperature"].resample("ME").mean()

# Normalize for visualization

# Choose a sample window

input_len = 24
forecast_len = 12
input_window = normalized_temp.iloc[start_idx:start_idx + input_len]

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

# Load major city data
df = pd.read_csv("/Users/rero/.cache/kagglehub/datasets/berkeleyearth/climate-change-earth-surface-temperature-data/versions/2/GlobalLandTemperaturesByMajorCity.csv")
df = df.dropna(subset=["AverageTemperature"])
df["dt"] = pd.to_datetime(df["dt"])

# Filter to year 2010
df_2010 = df[df["dt"].dt.year == 2010].copy()

# Latitude/Longitude conversion
df_2010["lat_num"] = df_2010["Latitude"].apply(lambda x: -float(x[:-1]) if "S" in x else float(x[:-1]))
df_2010["lon_num"] = df_2010["Longitude"].apply(lambda x: -float(x[:-1]) if "W" in x else float(x[:-1]))

# Binning
lat_bins = np.arange(-90, 91, 5)
lon_bins = np.arange(-180, 181, 5)
df_2010["lat_bin"] = pd.cut(df_2010["lat_num"], bins=lat_bins)
df_2010["lon_bin"] = pd.cut(df_2010["lon_num"], bins=lon_bins)

# Grid avg
grid = df_2010.groupby(["lat_bin", "lon_bin"], observed=True)["AverageTemperature"].mean().unstack()

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.imshow(grid.to_numpy(), cmap="coolwarm", interpolation="nearest", aspect="auto", origin="lower")
plt.title("Spatial Grid of City Temperatures (2010) with Missing Data Masked", fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel("Longitude Bins")
plt.ylabel("Latitude Bins")
plt.colorbar(label="Avg Temp (°C)")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("slide8_spatial_grid_masking.png", dpi=300)
plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

# Simulated training and validation loss values
epochs = np.arange(1, 51)
train_loss = np.exp(-0.1 * epochs) + 0.02 * np.random.randn(len(epochs))
val_loss = np.exp(-0.1 * epochs) + 0.02 * np.random.randn(len(epochs))
val_loss[20:] += 0.03 * np.arange(len(val_loss[20:]))

# Identify early stopping point
early_stop_epoch = 25

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.plot(epochs, train_loss, label="Training Loss", color="blue", linewidth=2)
plt.plot(epochs, val_loss, label="Validation Loss", color="orange", linewidth=2)
plt.axvline(early_stop_epoch, color="red", linestyle="--", label=f"Early Stopping (Epoch {early_stop_epoch})")

plt.title("Training vs Validation Loss with Early Stopping", fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel("Epoch")
plt.ylabel("Loss")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True, linestyle="--", alpha=0.4)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("slide9_training_curve.png", dpi=300)
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
import numpy as np

# Load global dataset
df = pd.read_csv("/Users/rero/.cache/kagglehub/datasets/berkeleyearth/climate-change-earth-surface-temperature-data/versions/2/GlobalTemperatures.csv")
df = df[["dt", "LandAverageTemperature"]].dropna()
df["dt"] = pd.to_datetime(df["dt"])
df = df[df["dt"].dt.year >= 1900]

# Resample to annual average
df.set_index("dt", inplace=True)
annual_temp = df["LandAverageTemperature"].resample("YE").mean().dropna()
years = np.array([d.year for d in annual_temp.index]).reshape(-1, 1)
temps = annual_temp.values

# Fit linear model as baseline predictor
model = LinearRegression()
model.fit(years, temps)
preds = model.predict(years)

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
plt.plot(annual_temp.index, temps, label="Actual Temperature", color="blue")
plt.plot(annual_temp.index, preds, label="Predicted Trend (Linear)", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Global Land Temperature: Actual vs. Predicted Trend", fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel("Year")
plt.ylabel("Average Temperature (°C)")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True, linestyle="--", alpha=0.4)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("slide12_warming_trend.png", dpi=300)
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load country data
df = pd.read_csv("/Users/rero/.cache/kagglehub/datasets/berkeleyearth/climate-change-earth-surface-temperature-data/versions/2/GlobalLandTemperaturesByCountry.csv")
df = df.dropna(subset=["AverageTemperature"])
df["dt"] = pd.to_datetime(df["dt"])

# Focus on Russia (high-latitude, strong seasonal cycles)
df = df[df["Country"] == "Russia"]
df = df[df["dt"].dt.year >= 1900]

# Monthly rolling standard deviation (seasonal amplitude proxy)
df.set_index("dt", inplace=True)
monthly_std = df["AverageTemperature"].rolling(window=12, center=True).std()

# Smooth the signal (yearly avg of rolling std)
monthly_std_annual = monthly_std.resample("YE").mean()

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
plt.plot(monthly_std_annual.index, monthly_std_annual, color="darkgreen", linewidth=2)
plt.title("Evolution of Seasonal Temperature Amplitude in Russia", fontsize=14)

plt.ylabel("Rolling Std Dev (°C) – 12-Month Window")
plt.grid(True, linestyle="--", alpha=0.4)
plt.tight_layout()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load data
city_df = pd.read_csv("/Users/rero/.cache/kagglehub/datasets/berkeleyearth/climate-change-earth-surface-temperature-data/versions/2/GlobalLandTemperaturesByMajorCity.csv")
country_df = pd.read_csv("/Users/rero/.cache/kagglehub/datasets/berkeleyearth/climate-change-earth-surface-temperature-data/versions/2/GlobalLandTemperaturesByCountry.csv")

# Clean and filter
city_df = city_df[(city_df["City"] == "Toronto") & (city_df["Country"] == "Canada")].dropna(subset=["AverageTemperature"])
country_df = country_df[country_df["Country"] == "Canada"].dropna(subset=["AverageTemperature"])
city_df["dt"] = pd.to_datetime(city_df["dt"])
country_df["dt"] = pd.to_datetime(country_df["dt"])

# Monthly resampling
city_temp = city_df.set_index("dt")["AverageTemperature"].resample("ME").mean()
country_temp = country_df.set_index("dt")["AverageTemperature"].resample("ME").mean()

# Align time
df = pd.DataFrame({
    "City": city_temp,
    "Country": country_temp
}).dropna()

# Compute smoothed difference
df["UHI_Diff"] = df["City"] - df["Country"]
df["UHI_Smoothed"] = df["UHI_Diff"].rolling(window=12, center=True).mean()

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(13, 5))
sns.set(style="whitegrid")
plt.plot(df.index, df["UHI_Smoothed"], color="firebrick", linewidth=2)
plt.axhline(0, linestyle="--", color="gray", alpha=0.6)
plt.title("Urban Heat Island Effect: Toronto vs. Canada", fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel("Year")
plt.ylabel("12-Month Smoothed Temp Difference (°C)")
plt.grid(True, linestyle="--", alpha=0.3)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("slide14_urban_heat_island.png", dpi=300)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load country data
df = pd.read_csv("/Users/rero/.cache/kagglehub/datasets/berkeleyearth/climate-change-earth-surface-temperature-data/versions/2/GlobalLandTemperaturesByCountry.csv")
df = df.dropna(subset=["AverageTemperature"])
df["dt"] = pd.to_datetime(df["dt"])

# Extract year and continent mapping (simplified manual map)
continent_map = {
    "Africa": ["South Africa", "Egypt", "Morocco", "Nigeria", "Algeria", "Kenya"],
    "Asia": ["Russia", "India", "China", "Japan", "South Korea", "Indonesia"],
    "Europe": ["Germany", "France", "Italy", "Spain", "United Kingdom", "Sweden"],
    "North America": ["Canada", "United States", "Mexico"],
    "South America": ["Brazil", "Argentina", "Chile"],
    "Oceania": ["Australia", "New Zealand"]
}

# Reverse lookup: country → continent
country_to_continent = {
    country: continent
    for continent, countries in continent_map.items()
    for country in countries
}

df["year"] = df["dt"].dt.year
df["continent"] = df["Country"].map(country_to_continent)
df = df.dropna(subset=["continent"])

# Count records per year per continent
heatmap_data = df.groupby(["year", "continent"]).size().unstack().fillna(0)

# Focus on historical coverage window
heatmap_data = heatmap_data[heatmap_data.index <= 1950]

# Plot heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.heatmap(heatmap_data.T, cmap="YlOrRd", linewidths=0.2, linecolor="gray")
plt.title("Data Coverage by Continent (Years ≤ 1950)", fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel("Year")
plt.ylabel("Continent")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("slide18_data_challenges.png", dpi=300)
plt.show()
